your credit-worthiness. Quizzle gives you your free score from Experian, plus a few other financial tools.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There are a lot of scams out there about getting "free" credit reports and scores, but this one doesn't ask for your credit card or Social Security number, isn't a trial, and is provided by Quicken Loans. So you will get offers for refinancing and credit monitoring, much like you get sponsored offers in Mint, but for the free credit score, those ads may be worth it. If you want access to monthly credit reports and scores, plus credit monitoring, that service is $7 a month, which is still pretty cheap and may be useful for guarding against identity theft.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to giving you your credit report and score from Experian one time for free, Quizzle analyzes your debt burden and shows you how much available cash you have each month based on the information you provide when signing up (income, savings, and homeownership).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will probably still want to check all three credit bureaus' reports from Annual Credit Report each year, and get your scores from them before applying for a loan, but this is a free resource for getting your score at least from one of the bureaus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="http://cache.gawker.com/assets/images/lifehacker/2011/02/style-attribution-arrow-2.png" title="Quizzle Gives You a Free Credit Score and Credit Report" alt="Quizzle Gives You a Free Credit Score and Credit Report" height="20" width="19"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.quizzle.com"&gt;Quizzle&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
